article.headline: Fla. International 80, Monmouth, N.J. 61
article.story: Miami -- Michael Dominguez scored 22 points and Nikola Gacesa added 20 as Florida International defeated Monmouth 80-61 Monday night. Russell Hicks added 12 points, and Cedric Essola had a game-high 10 rebounds as the Golden Panthers (2-0)forced 13 turnovers. Travis Taylor led the way for Monmouth (0-2), scoring 13 points and grabbing five rebounds. Florida International had a good night from behind the 3-point arc, hitting 8 of 16 shots. The Golden Panthers also out rebounded Monmouth 36-26 in the victory. Florida International went into the locker room leading Monmouth 43-24 before the teams scored 39 points each in the second half.
